displayName: Things to add or fix before going live

items.description: Need to add timestamp for when comments are made.
Set up data in its own private repo for more security

items.feedback: Adding items at the same time works great. Updating items does not work. Deleting items that aren't updated at the same time might work.

items.description: Set max-height/max characters for card display in columns. End with ellipsis or fade out or something so the cards don't get huge and take up too much space. There is a description limit of 500 characters, so they can't take up a whole page, but darn this is one long description that I don't want to display fully on a task's card. This is so long I only want it to fully show when you've opened the task modal.
Remove image thumbnails from card view and replace with icon and number.
items.feedback:
I like the quick preview of if/what images are attached. Let me know if you think it's too much, because I can put an icon with a number instead.

This is crap, you can't stop me!

items.description: Make the type (Change Request, Issue, Feature) completely admin only. Customers don't know the difference and we usually have to set this ourselves anyway.
Add Employ Logo at the top since we should represent that we are apart of that. I think there is a marketing site for that?
When not in admin mode, some of these columns should be hidden when empty. Specifically, the "Feedback", "In progress" and "Re-test" columns should be hidden when empty.
Add customer name, UAT deadline and dev link info.
items.feedback: Add a way to edit this in the admin UI

items.description: Don't default all task types to "Change Request" on creation

Multiple UAT instances for single accounts. If a customer has multi-lingual, internal/external, subsidiaries, etc., it could be nice to not have to create a new account each time and have all UATs in one account.
items.feedback: This is probably possible in the future, but would require a significant refactor of how data is handled so I'm going to cancel this for this version.
